Spring Boot

Spring framework + Embedded HTTP Server  + xml configuration  = Spring Boot Application
                     (Tomcat, Jetty)

Advantages of Spring boot
 -> stand-alone using -jar 
 -> Embedded Http server such Tomcat, Jetty etc..,
 -> starter (POM) to Maven configuration
 -> Production ready - log, metrics, health checks
 -> pulgins , testing 
 -> Admin support

properties files: Application.properties // src/resources 
    default spring boot localhost:8080 (port number) 

YAML Support : JSON 

Spring MVC , Rest, Dynamic web apps, Easy frontend integration , API, HTTP (request/response)
Spring security , OAuth2 , Eureka

DI Annotations:

@Autowired - Injects dependencies field, constructor, setter.

Class Employee{
@Autowired
private Address address;

}

@Qualifer

specifies which bean multiple bean student 1, 2, 3(@qualifer)

@Primary 

specifies default which bean multiple bean student 1, 2, 3, 4(@Primary)

@Bean - configuration class to specifiy 

@Scope - ***

(Singleton, prototype)

@Value

@Lazy 
Class Rep -


Context Configuration :

@Profile("dev") //dev, uat, qa, prod

@Import
@ImportResource

@PropertySoruce

Core Annotations:
  "@SpringBootApplication"
      1) Configuration - marks class configuration source
      2) EnableAutoConfiguration - automatically configures bean(magic spring boot)
      3) ComponentScan - Scans packages 

      
